place.name: WEST WORLDHAM
place.gazetteerText: WORLDHAM (West), a parish in Alton district, Hants; 2 miles SE of Alton r. station. Post town, Alton. Acres, 447. Real property, £640. Pop., 89. Houses, 16. A tumulus is on King John's hill, and fragments of Roman pottery have been found there. The living is a vicarage in the diocese of Winchester. Value, £38. Patron, Winchester College. The church is good (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
